    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation for model risk level 3. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved 2, required 3) is accepted under a risk-informed rationale: the single ASTM F1717 load offset represents the clinically bounding scenario, and the overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission claim for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under static compression-bending loading.",
